The introduction of technical assessments seems to reduce competition and raise the procurement costs. When technical thresholds are established, the average number of bidders declines slightly from 4.9 to 4.6. The normalized average bid would increase from 0.95 to 1.18 (Table 1
). In the probability distributions, it is clear that the number of bidders conditional on the presence of substantive technical evaluation is distributed in the lower tail (Figure 2
). The relative bid, though less clear, looks to concentrate more on the left-hand side when some technical evaluation process is adopted (Figure 3
).

